{"title": "Confessions of a Book-Lover", "description": "\"I am of the company of book men who read simply for the love of it,\" confesses E. Walter Walters, in this gently written tome. Walters documents his habit of \"book fishing--\" seeking and finding quality volumes in the discount binds at his booksellers, and as a connoisseur of wine might match varieties with courses, he matches his books with the contexts in which he reads them--in the garden, in the bedroom, with friends. He also provides a list of his favorite authors (mostly 19th century United Kingdom) and favorite books, as well as favorite characters from the books he has read, not in a way to impose his choices on other readers, but to share his own personal experiences. (summary by Dr. P. Gould)", "duration": 7489, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "12799", "name": "E. Walter Walters"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/confessions_book-lover_1708_librivox/booklover_1708.jpg", "copyright_year": "1913", "genres": ["Essays & Short Works", "Writing & Linguistics"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "DrPGould"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "DrPGould"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Availle"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Tom Penn"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introduction", "readers": [11651], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/confessions_book-lover_1708_librivox/confessionsbooklover_00_walters_64kb.mp3", "duration": 372}, {"section": 1, "title": "Ch. 1 'Humbly to Confess'", "readers": [11651], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/confessions_book-lover_1708_librivox/confessionsbooklover_01_walters_64kb.mp3", "duration": 637}, {"section": 2, "title": "Ch. 2 Books & Gardens", "readers": [11651], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/confessions_book-lover_1708_librivox/confessionsbooklover_02_walters_64kb.mp3", "duration": 522}, {"section": 3, "title": "Ch. 3 Books that Tempt", "readers": [11651], "path": "http://www.archive.org